reviewText: complete package arrived in a timely fashion

B J King is a little hard to follow when she's a little bland, good thing she moves around a lot.  The program feels very much like an introductory course, and as such, I see it as a stepping stone to much more interesting work.
The title refers to human behavior, author talks of primate behavior, and lumps humans among apes.
Overall, I'd say say it's a good place to start if you're interested primate behavior.
This is weak when it comes to anything beyond simple primate behavior.
